olive oil
1 Carrot
1 Courgette
1 packet Roasted almonds
¾ cup water
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 packet couscous
2 packet Halloumi
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 tsp honey
1 packet Baby Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet parsley
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Grate carrot.
• Thinly slice courgette into half-moons.
• Roughly chop roasted almonds.

• In a medium saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook carrot and courgette, stirring, until softened, 3-4 minutes.
• Add the water and vegetable stock powder and bring to the boil.
• Add couscous and stir to combine. Cover with a lid and remove from heat.
• Set aside until all the water is absorbed, 5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork.

 • Meanwhile, cut haloumi into 1cm-thick slices.
• In a large bowl, combine haloumi, garlic & herb seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook haloumi, until golden brown, 1-2 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Remove from heat, then add the honey and turn to coat.

• Add baby leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil to the couscous. Season and gently toss to combine.
• Divide veggie couscous between bowls.
• Top with haloumi and sprinkle with roasted almonds.
• Tear over parsley and top with a dollop of Greek-style yoghurt to serve. Enjoy!